            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;The :focus-within CSS pseudo-class matches an element if the element or any of its descendants are focused.&lt;/code&gt; It &lt;a href=&quot;https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/:focus-within&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;works&lt;/a&gt; with every element, not just &lt;code&gt;input&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/3789527/ls&quot; title=&quot;6,464 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;LS_&lt;/a&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment122086033_56897698&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2021-09-06 15:36:59Z, License: CC BY-SA 4.0&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Sep 6, 2021 at 15:36&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
