&lt;p&gt;How do I select the &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;li&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; element that is a direct parent of the anchor element?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an example, my CSS would be something like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;default s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-css&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-selector-tag&quot;&gt;li&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt; &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-selector-tag&quot;&gt;a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-selector-class&quot;&gt;.active&lt;/span&gt; {
    property: value;
}
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Obviously there are ways of doing this with JavaScript, but I&apos;m hoping that there is some sort of workaround that exists native to CSS Level 2.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The menu that I am trying to style is being spewed out by a CMS, so I can&apos;t move the active element to the &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;li&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; element... (unless I theme the menu creation module which I&apos;d rather not do).&lt;/p&gt;
